Question:
You are given an array nums1
of n
| distinct integers.
You want to construct another array nums2 of length n such that the elements in (nums2 are either all odd or all even.
For each index i, you must choose exactly one of the following (in any order):
• nums2 [i] = nums1[i]
nums2[i] = nums|[i] - nums|[i]), for an index j != i, such that nums1[il - numsiljl >= 1
Return true if it is possible to construct such an array, otherwise return false.
Example 1:
Input: nums1 = [1,4,7]
Output: true
Explanation:
• Set nums2[Ø] = nums1[0] = 1.
• Set |nums2[1] = nums1[1] - nums1[0] = 4 - 1 = 3).
• Set nums2[2] = nums1[2] = 7.
nums2 = 1, 3, 7l, and all elements are odd. Thus, the answer is true.

Solution:
class Solution {
    public boolean uniformArray(int[] nums1) {
        int i,n = nums1.length;
        for(i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums1[i]%2==1)
                break;
        }
        if(i==n) return true;
        int odd=0;
        Arrays.sort(nums1);
        for(i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums1[i]%2==1) odd++;
            else if(odd==0) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
